                            <comment id="13893632" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 18:36:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(Tagged &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=krummas&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;krummas&quot;&gt;krummas&lt;/a&gt; for review.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13893806" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 21:02:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 changes count to long (pointed out by Paulo Gaspar, who brought this to my attention initially)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13894284" author="krummas" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2014 08:06:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;looks like we have the same bug in getMeanRowSize()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(seems v2 got committed in trunk with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6671&quot; title=&quot;NoSuchElementException in trunk&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6671&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6671&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13894569" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2014 14:37:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, they&apos;re computing different things, so meanRowSize looks correct to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will fix the CHANGES record.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13894679" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2014 16:19:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;... you&apos;re right, I was misreading the CFM code.  Committed (after reverting the accidental trunk commit to keep things clean).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
